@NODE RM_COMP "Amiga Compatibility?"
    Well, in theory it should work any Amiga with at least 1MB.
  In practice however, things are far less pleasant.
    It only works on Amiga's with 1MB+ and requires at least a
  Kickstart of 2.0 or more. Anything less than that then the Amiga does
  it's guru thang and sulks in a corner.
    Whether this has anything to do with Blitz or my programming I don't
  honestly know.

  What I @{" recommend " LINK rm_rec} you play it on however, is a different story.

    Also bear in mind It's been a while since I tested this on other
  machines. Last I tried it worked on the A600 and A1200.

    If you are using this on an Amiga Emulator such as UAE I'm afraid
  it won't work due to it's unfinished parallel port emulation. It always
  regards players 3 and 4 as constantly holding fire. Perhaps this will
  improve in future releases. Here's hoping.

    @{" Troubleshooting " LINK rm_shit}
@ENDNODE

