@NODE RM_HIST "Programmer's History"
    The game began life a long while ago due to the laziness of a friend
  of mine @{"Angus Arthur" LINK rm_credits} who refused to do anything
  with a great two player game of his called Kill each other Violently.
    It was also due in part to a PD offering called Extreme Violence.
  The games in themselves were good but could have been so much more
    I decided this could be improved upon and began to write my own AMOS.

    This was quickly scrapped. As friendly as AMOS BASIC is I'd have been
  better off writing it in Speccy BASIC thanks to it's chronic speed. The
  game slowed down on 2 players before a single shot was fired. This
  failure was quickly scrapped.

    Then about a year later I bought the God-Like Blitz Basic 2 and my
  prayers were answered. At the end of '94 I began work on Cold Blooded
  Murder.
    Since than I've spent about 4 or 5 hours a week tinkering with it.
  It really has grown into something rather unexpected. I never expected
  it to be nearly as good as it turned out to be.


@ENDNODE

