@NODE RM_REC "Recommended gear"
  For a truly great game you need the following,

*   2MB Chip RAM
      On 1MB there is no room for Sound Effects. God Damn, that's one of
    the most impressive bits of this game. Go and buy an expansion right
    now.

*   68020 Processer
      Without a piece of kit that runs at least 14 M/hz your 4 & 5 player
    games will run at horrible speeds. You also lose out on many snazzy
    effects like spraying blood and teleport sparkles.

*   AGA chipset
      Without this your game will lose much of it's atmosphere. The
    chipset will give you nicer loading screens, smoother animations and
    best of all gorgeous fade effects, including the bright flashes from
    explosive weapons.

*   Four Player Adaptor
      This is a cheap bit of wire that dangles out the Parallel port.
    This is ESSENTIAL for a truly good game of Murder.
    3 player games are as nothing to the chaos of a 5 player game of
    5 evenly matched players.

*  Four Good Joysticks
     It's not much fun being stuck on a mates old Atari 2600 joystick.
   Try to make sure everyone is comfortable with their controller. Make
   your friends bring their favourite joysticks from home, why should you
   fork out.
     You'd also better hope that at least one of you are comfortable on
   keyboard. Probably the ex-Speccy owner will fit this category.

*  A bloody great big Stereo
     Preferably a powerful one through which explosions can rumble.
   The music isn't up to much, but the sound is something I am very
   proud of. It fits the manic pace of the game nicely. From the pained
   screams of each player to the deep roar of a flame thrower it's
   all rather splendid in stereo.

*  A bloody great big Monitor
     All the graphics were drawn on a monitor, and the game is best
   appreciated on a monitor. The smaller bullets are difficult to spot
   on the fuzz of a TV set.

*  A Hard Disk
     Obviously, and if you don't own one you deserve to wallow in your
   slow access times.

* 1MB Fast RAM
     Not only do 020 owners get a couple of extra effects but the game
   never slows down, no matter what massive destruction is occurring
   on screen. Slow-down is rare on a vanilla A1200 but it happens.

*  Four good losers
     Murder is one of those amazingly competitive games that can annoy
   everyone involved.


    If you have all of these, I refuse to believe you do not enjoy this
  game.
@ENDNODE

@NODE RM_BUGS "Known Bugs"
  The mere mention of a bug is enough to make a programmer shiver.

    Almost every game has 'em, and this is no different.

*  Very occasionally a player will find himself able to shoot far more
   often than is normal. I've no idea why. This happens most often with
   the Xenon Laser.

*  Williams, the Red Player, is not always red. Due to the surreal
   AGA sprite handling the Amiga decides to fetch his palette from
   some unknown place in the memory rather than the usual registers.
   This happens at odd times, and with no change to the code.

*  Sometime the shop will just refuse to sell items no matter how much
   money a player has.

*  Once in a blue moon the system will simply crash. This is the most
   annoying bug of the lot, I have no idea why it does this.

  That's all I know about. @{"e-mail" LINK rm_simon} if you find others.

@ENDNODE

